17 Sec. 13d. (1) The wages and fringe benefits fund is created in
18 the state treasury.
19 (2) The state treasurer shall deposit money and other assets
20 received from any source into the fund. The state treasurer shall
21 direct the investment of the money in the fund and credit interest
22 and earnings from the investments to the fund.
23 (3) Money in the fund at the close of the fiscal year must
24 remain in the fund and not lapse to the general fund.
25 (4) The department is the administrator of the fund for
26 auditing purposes.
27 (5) The department shall expend money from the fund, upon
28 appropriation, only to enforce this act.
